filling - terminal-based text editor

Description:
The 'filling' program is a lightweight terminal text editor that allows you to create, view, and edit text files. It supports basic cursor movement, text insertion, deletion, and saving. If a file with the ".c" extension is opened, C syntax highlighting is automatically enabled. Non-text files are opened in read-only mode with a warning.

Usage:
filling [<filename>]

Examples:
filling
filling notes.txt
filling program.c
